"e=3D"font-size:16px">It is observed that Play ransomware affiliates are pot=" || filename = "entially using new or updated Tactics, Techniques and Procedures (TTPs) whi=" || filename = "ch includes After getting initial access, ad=" || filename = "versary enrolls at least one new device in the customer's Multi Factor Auth=" || filename = "entication (MFA) portal from IP addresses, identified as VPN nodes associat=" || filename = "ed with SurfShark VPN and BlueVPS. Adversary then attempts to bypass MFA by=" || filename = "calling the organization=E2=80=99s helpdesk to get the MFA factor changed.=" || filename = "Using a compromised account, the adversary downloads SharpSpray and carrie=" || filename = "s out behaviors consistent with known Play ransomware TTPs like harvesting =" || filename = "credentials by dumping memory and LSASS processes and collecting the SAM an=" || filename = "d SYSTEM registry hives from several hosts. Finally, adversary gains access=" || filename = "to a service account, achieving privilege escalation, and then gains acces=" || filename = "s to a domain controller. The adversary proceeds to extract and exfiltrate =" || filename = "=E2=80=9CNTDS.dit,=E2=80=9D an Active Directory domain database containing =" || filename = "credentials for lateral movement.&nbsp;</span></font><br></div><div style=" || filename = "=3D"color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );font-family:'verdana' , 'arial' , 'helvetica' , =" || filename = Out-of-bound memory access in WebGL2 blitFramebuffer, Use after free in MessagePort::Entangled and ReadableByteStreamQueueEntry::Buffer, Clickjacking permission prompts using the fullscreen Clickjacking to load insecure pages in HTTPS-only mode, Memory safety bugs, Privilege escalation through <a [referrerpolicy]> in ReaderMode, HTML injection in %READER-BYLINE% of ReaderMode. A remote attacker could exploit these vulnerabilities by persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web site." || filename = "" || filename = "Successful exploitation of these vulnerabilities "e=3D"font-size:16px">It is observed that Play ransomware affiliates are pot=" || filename = "entially using new or updated Tactics, Techniques and Procedures (TTPs) whi=" || filename = "ch includes the use of SharpSpray, an open source Windows password spraying=" || filename = "tool, use of IP addresses associated with SurfShark and BlueVPS VPN/VPS pr=" || filename = "oviders, and voice phishing (aka vishing). After getting initial access, ad=" || filename = "versary enrolls at least one new device in the customer's Multi Factor Auth=" || filename = "entication (MFA) portal from IP addresses, identified as VPN nodes associat=" || filename = "ed with SurfShark VPN and BlueVPS. Adversary then attempts to bypass MFA by=" || filename = "calling the organization=E2=80=99s helpdesk to get the MFA factor changed.=" || filename = "Using a compromised account, the adversary downloads SharpSpray and carrie=" || filename = "s out behaviors consistent with known Play ransomware TTPs like harvesting =" || filename = "credentials by dumping memory and LSASS processes and collecting the SAM an=" || filename = "d SYSTEM registry hives from several hosts. Finally, adversary gains access=" || filename = "to a service account, achieving privilege escalation, and then gains acces=" || filename = "s to a domain controller. movement.&nbsp;</span></font><br></div><div style=" || filename = "=3D"color:rgb( 0 , 0 , 0 );font-family:'verdana' , 'arial' , 'helvetica' , =" || filename =
